--> Skip DNS Lookup
nmap -n <target>
Doesn't try to resolve IP addresses to hostnames.
Use when: You want faster scans and don't need hostnames.

--> Force DNS Lookup
nmap -R <target>
Always tries to resolve IPs to hostnames.
Use when: You want to see device names on the network.

--> Fragment Packets
nmap -f <target>
Breaks packets into smaller pieces.
Use when: Trying to bypass simple firewalls or packet filters.

--> Use Decoys
nmap -D RND:10 <target>
Sends packets from 10 random fake IPs along with yours.
Use when: Hiding your real IP during a scan.
